Diary of Shiyan: that little place called figs

By Wang Nian Jun.

Isou took the high-speed train home.

The high-speed train goes through Gucheng County.

Gucheng County is followed by long tunnels, into the mountains, like Vaginas, into which live the peoples of the outside world.

Out here is the plain

Out here, you're an adult

When Meng Haoran stopped in Xiangyang, he looked out at the mountains to the northwest, where other mountains were buried and where people lived, a sparsely populated hinterland of Chinese culture. Since then, there has been less documentation of civilisation and less interaction, with the Yangtze turning into Wu Gorge from the south-west and Han River from the north-west.

"The new Tang Book Lu Xiang first biography" has "the world this is nothing, mediocre people disturb it for the annoying ear" , later simplified as "mediocre people disturb themselves" . "Yong" is also Shiyan Zhushan County within the territory of the ancient country name, so attached will be the source of this idiom.

Han Bi's poem "Spring Ploughing in Shiyan" in the Ming Dynasty, "the river is full of water in the sound of Bugu, the plough is ploughed in the south and the north. Until 1960s, when Shiyan, northwest of Hubei, was carved out of thatch and filled with technicians from Wuhan and elsewhere as a city of immigrants, old Shiyan Street had only three main roads that were askew.

Meanwhile, my brother-in-law was finishing his dinner and heading for Shiyan East station.

In a day, our story will shrink to a place called fig land, a street-level district in Zhangwan District, Shiyan.

Now I want to give the reader the geographical, economic and cultural background of the place before the other characters come out.

The flowers are in Shiyan

The settlement was formed in large part by the location of the 64th and 62nd branches of the "Second Automobile" (Dongfeng No. 2 Automobile Factory) in a valley to the north of the government-owned corporation, there are hospitals, parks, family buildings, office buildings, farmers'markets, kindergartens and even high schools. As a result, the site became prosperous after the factory was located. Now, the annual average operating rate is insufficient, the technical production capacity is moved out, as the factory efficiency is increasingly depressed, the flower and fruit as the urbanized population net migration area, but also to the city center, Wuhan exported a lot of talents, especially the young labor force and skilled workers.

The summer floods that killed civilians, the occasional car accident, a few days' strike by a car company, the rectification of the "big market" and the regulation of the river in Zhuhe are all subjects of endless discussion. It's so normal to be here and everything that's going on, if you've been in any other small city in China, you know what I mean.

The terrain is close to the hills and mountains, with China National Highway 316 and XiangyangChongqing Railway running through it, and the city is banded along the more gentle valleys, as if it were a national highway. In a slightly open area and in recent years the newly-built industrial park in Kaishanpingtu is the site of the "Second Automobile" and a small number of other industrial plants. The line is a must for travellers travelling from Chongqing to Wuhan, but people pay little attention to the place they cross. Even people who live in Shiyan and have to pass through it don't pay attention to it.

Its houses along the street look low and gray, not exactly suburban, but certainly not what you'd expect in a central core city. To put it crudely, it is like a city's anus, a excretory organ on which thousands of elderly people, the first generation of migrant workers, now in their sixty, have piled up. Unable to afford to live in the "central city" east of Hongwei, they settled in the undeveloped land between them.

Further West, through the Yan West "economic development zone" , walk about the same distance (about 10 kilometers) , is the town of Berlin (formerly known as Berlin for its Cypress Trees). Some residents also say that when Shiyan was founded, it made a grand industrial plan. Because it is west of Shiyan, it is called "West Berlin" , which means "three years to catch up with Britain, five years to be Super Beautiful") , further West is Huanglong town, which is also a small distribution center. It is already the edge of the city and is now under the jurisdiction of Yunyang District (the old Yunyang territory) in its valley, visitors walking along the shore will see a large vegetable base covered with white plastic sheeting, most of which is used to supply daily life in the city.

Shiyan's car production capacity has been shrinking since 2003, when the company moved its headquarters to Wuhan, and the period between then and 2015 was the fastest-growing period of urbanisation in the region. Many of the area of flowers and fruits originally belong to the "two steam" family housing, housing owners have been moved to the city (such as Liuyan, Wuyan, Sanyan) or the provincial capital of Wuhan. Much of the vacant housing has been handed over to the first generation of migrant workers. Thus, migrant workers can gather in the flowers and fruits.

In this nearly 17-year period, it is also a process of gradual depletion of residential facilities in the flower and fruit areas (including "family buildings" , small parks, badminton courts, etc.) . The original movie theater has become a hospital and a clothing supermarket, bookstores, video stores, beauty salons, basketball courts and swimming pools are all disappearing, replaced by convenience stores and humble barber shops, mobile phone salons, fruit shops and delivery outlets.

Shiyan is an aging city, especially outside the city center, including the suburbs and the countryside. On flower and Fruit Street, you can see many funeral clothes, fire paper, wreath shops, even one for tens of meters in a crowded place, there are also many recreational facilities and shops for the elderly. Chess and card room, fishing gear shop, middle-aged and old people's health care shop, health care gift shop, or directly to the "elderly activity center" as the name of the leisure place, the streets are full of people aged over 50 years old. In addition to the Spring Festival, the young and middle-aged population are often in the field, home school children are often led by the elderly. They wore mostly black leather jackets, black corduroy pants, and heavy boots, and their hands were habitually tucked into the pockets of their jackets when traveling or talking to people.

These places are more like hidden backwater bays

Almost every year in Shiyan, construction sites are everywhere, everywhere in the development of tourism, such as Yunyang district, has recently developed Wuzixu Lake, Yunyang School Palace, dinosaur egg fossil site, Longquan SI scenic tourist area. On this trip home, Isou even saw a blue road sign near the Hongyu Hotel at No. 3 station that read: "Huaguo mountain scenic area, 2.3 kilometers north to No. 6 and No. 4 factory. ".

The initial buildings of the various tourism projects are everywhere, often showing the rudiments of the future, but for now they are vibrant and unsightly. Roads, highways, bridges, and other infrastructure are being built every year, and there is plenty of open land that has been bulldozed and left barren for months. The memory of the older generation still retains the impression that it is necessary to cross the ferry to Yunxian city and Wufeng. However, now there are more than three bridges in Yunyang district.

Beyond these changes, on the outskirts of the city, or in the Old City, there are still places like flowers and fruits, where we find traces of humanity being degraded by time. Although the peak, the new buildings will add two or three every year, but the old buildings, together with the new, are rapidly declining.

Some bright paint is on the exterior walls of old streetscape houses and residential buildings. Human tinkering never seems to catch up with the weathering and mottling of the lime and red brick that are so often exposed to the elements. In recent years, in particular, the grassroots government seems to have received a great deal of funding -- supposedly as a result of an inspection by the Standing Committee -- as if to restore parts that do not look tidy enough. But once you turn into an alley off the main road, you see decade-old "Cotton Gin" signs, signs for public restrooms in crudely Red Ochre, old iron cables on bridges, and the private sector, which has long since stopped working.

These places are more like hidden migratory bays than the visible changes of time elsewhere, and only the observant and long-term inhabitants of one place will not lose sight of the immense encroachments of time. Things continue to change, but at a speed you can't see with the naked eye, and when you look back in a few years, you'll be amazed at the near-extinction rate.

Most of the buildings, except perhaps for the factories, are on the opposite side of the idiom, as flakes from the fishmonger's steel knife, scattered randomly over the damp waters beneath his apron. In terms of paralysis, FIG's symptoms closely resemble those of James Joyce's Dublin in the early 20th century. ISOU has spent only the Spring Festival and summer holidays here for a decade, but each time he returns, his calendar is as if it had never been updated, and vendors are always hawking vegetables, fruits, couplets and household goods along the street. Although the district committee set a fixed point for trading activities, built a rain shelter, but less than half a year, the road police can not maintain order. An outsider needs only a glimpse of the face of any resident on the street to know what is on his mind. The grains and the sesame seeds piled up in their hearts and in the bottom of their chests are piled up on their sly or almost dull faces, as if they were little changed in appearance, but gradually aged and covered with waxy wrinkles. They don't seem like the same race as the hip young men and women in the Central Mall, although the latter are often the children of the former.

Once, I remember, Isou ran away from his brother in law's house and walked along a deserted river course in the winter. It was a sort of SouthNorth Water Transfer Project of the Middle Route Project. The Zhuhe River crossing the city was an inconspicuous tributary of the Han River River, so the "upper" did some treatment on it. The riverbank was originally covered with barnyard grass, there are also small patches of land planted by local residents with vegetable moss, canola or Cress, piles of uncleared garbage under piers and, in some places, mounds of industrial waste; on rainy days, the river will overflow the road under the third station, making it impassable to traffic.

After the treatment, the river was cleaned up and the two sides were paved with a path of brick and stone, which could be passed by two people in parallel. Every few hundred meters, there are wooden ladders, bridges, or laid stepping stones to cross the river. But no matter how much you fix it, the landscape looks underdeveloped. The concrete manhole covers looked old and jarring, standing more than a foot above the lawn at a distance of 300 meters, and the brick floors were unpolished. The new man-made marks soon became old, the wood paint faded, the carved stone railings were smashed by cars or idlers, and outside the planned community were tile-roofed houses to be demolished and factories not yet started, the "image projects" that had just been built, it reflects the decay of more places, and, as you know, new, good-looking things fade after a year or two. Every family, or extended family, has its own way of spending the year together. It is hard to imagine a year in which the family's Spring Festival group and New Year greetings, as we have described them, would end. In ISOU's twenty-seven, Chinese New Year always meant visiting relatives and friends. In his childhood in Shangliao, his father and uncle lived next door to his grandparents, such "neighbors" add up to less than 100. The way to celebrate the New Year is to go their own way. After each family has their New Year's dinner, the children come out by themselves to play in the Dojo, swing, set off fireworks, Ski, Play hide-and-seek, and compare lucky money.

On New Year's Eve, they cooked sausages and Bacon around the stove, hung on the bamboo board on the roof to dry for a year, cooked among the tender corn that dried in the summer, and boiled from two o'clock in the afternoon until it was dark, and it was snowing outside, and the house was on fire, and then mother said, okay, just share it. It's the best food of the year. From the Gable Wall, several people gathered together and brought a big tree trunk which had been sawed off. The wooden barrel was thick and often dried out for a winter. When the tree core was still dry, it was burned in the fire. A thick tree trunk could burn all night long, and there was still a small fire left the next morning, it is called "boil the root of the year. ".

From the beginning of the year, the mother fried a variety of New Year's food on the stove. Even after the kitchen had been electrified, she remembered to throw a little dough into the fire of the stove to comfort the cook, to thank the Kitchen God, and to ask him not to say anything bad when he went up to heaven and reported the news of the family, make sure you're fed and clothed for the next year.

Generally stay at home on the first day of the New Year, early in the morning, the mother will hold a bundle of firewood, lit a fire, known as "Bao Cai (material) . ". Later, when the principal saw the way the students handled their lunch, he could not bear to, after school at noon, the students went to the mountain to collect firewood and cook for themselves. It was the village school that was demolished by the village Secretary Sixteen years later, the students were summoned to the playground by the principal, surrounded by the sun flower beds where bees were flying. The principal told them that there were nearly 5,000 infected people all over the country, and they needed to be prevented in time, many to the mountains dug Kudzu root, Isatis Tinctoria, Herba EPIMEDII, Houttuynia, acid does not take root (acid wine forum root) used to make tea, under fire disinfection, to prevent "SARS" . When Isou returned home, he dug in the mountains. Even without SARS, the local farmers knew the basic herbs and occasionally dug up some tea in the summer. On the advice of the headmaster, Isou became even more interested, keeping an eye out for any herbs he might find on his way to graze cows and gather hogsheads. In the countryside in 2003, there was little influx of outsiders, the village committee did little mandatory prevention, and there were no cases in the whole village.

Douyin, Wechat and new immigrants

It was the first year that my father played Douyin, but he was fascinated. After the epidemic, he often held his cell phone in his arms for half a day and picked it up after dinner. If readers knew that his cell phone used to be used only for answering and dialing calls, to see how profound this change is.

He will see in Douyin some of the migrant workers on the topic of wage, as well as folk music, speak allegro, transsexual voice of the content, he is interested. Later, every time he turned on Douyin, the APP would push the content, his father did not know why. "You can learn a lot of things that other people don't know. You can learn a lot of things that other people don't know. There are so many different kinds of programs. You can adjust your content at any time according to the hot news and make it easy to read. "

Wechat is also a popular APP, the father learned how to send and Click on voice messages, but forgot the next day, and had to teach again, so repeated for four or five days. "It's all very complicated, " Isou explained, after 10 or 18 times, when Isou was tired of teaching his father but still wanted to learn how to shop online and scan qr codes, still hasn't made my father understand what a Qr code is. "You are not skilled now, after binding the bank card is not safe, in case one day the operation is wrong... " he finally gave up.

While it's easy for most people to operate on a touch screen for the "digital natives, " my father was cut off from the culture of smartphones from their earliest days until about a year ago, he still uses a "geriatrics machine" with buttons, which are used only for entering numbers. For more than a decade, he had no interest in "playing" with his mobile phone. In his view, the mobile phone is only entertainment, and not directly related to labor and money.

If the reader wants to understand the plight of ISOU's father without prejudice, and not simply to think that he is "intellectually diminished, " then you should put yourself in his shoes, not "epidemiology biology, " just a general cultural background, in your 50s, you face an expert to explain the Ncov Gene Identification Process, and let you memorize it, this will be difficult, because this knowledge is not embedded in your brain, it's so new and weird that it doesn't fit in with the rest of what you already know.

Despite constant learning in his life, my father was still unable to master the knowledge of Cell Phone "Signal" , "SIM card" , "software" , "download" and "Wifi" in the face of smartphones. The interface, the flowing screens, the pictures and the words on them, were like a spell that was being cast before him.

Typing Chinese characters into a dialog box by hand was a primal experience for him, his whole body calcified like an unrecordable disk, the needle spinning without leaving a note. The reason why I bother to tell this story, because it will affect his survival in the plague, because in 10 days, to February 12, he would have to buy the next day to eat vegetables, but also through the Qr Code submitted wechat program.

At that time, he read out word by word the conversation of each person in the family group, because not very skilled, often turn out is the family a week ago conversation, thought to be just happened. Often, he would finish one sentence and go back to the meaning of the next, and the meaning of the first and the last could not be connected.

He had the highest intelligence and ability to survive in the areas he knew best, such as work, household, and small circle of acquaintances, and if he recorded his experience of the things he knew best, it must be the richest encyclopedia in the field. However, he's like a rock with no access to the new tool, and he's like an alien with the basic operations of retweeting friends, liking, commenting.

From the day after ISOU's return to his home, to twenty-eight more days in isolation, he repeatedly reposted what he had seen on Wechat, share some popular videos on "Go Shiyan, " "this food is absolutely inedible, " as if to prove that he knows the world, but also brings him appropriate excitement, and thinks that everyone will be as novel as he is.

Later, he recited the "Song of the dynasties of Chinese history" and discovered a history he had never heard of before. "What Dynasty is it now? " He asked, "Since Chairman Mao came to power, is our title Qing or republic? I heard some tubeback master say that the Emperor Guangxu should not have died so early, but the country was cursed by sorcerers and was short two hundred and seventy years. "

Not only does the epidemic have a profound impact on our lives today, it will also occupy our memories and change our minds for a long time to come. We need more eyes to continue to observe and document the crises and changes of our time. These are sincere and weighty records, and we will keep them.
